<item>
            <title>[SOLR-14109] zkcli.sh and zkcli.bat barfs when LOG4J_PROPS is set</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14109</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I noticed this when running &lt;tt&gt;zkcli.sh&lt;/tt&gt; from solr&apos;s docker image. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/docker-solr/docker-solr/blob/master/8.3/Dockerfile&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;The docker image sets the variable &lt;tt&gt;LOG4J_PROPS&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, causing the zkcli script to pick up and use that logger instead of the console logger. Problem with that is that Solr&apos;s log4j2 config relies on the &lt;tt&gt;solr.log.dir&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;sysprop being set, which it is not when running this script.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So either fix the wrapper script to set &lt;tt&gt;solr.log.dir&lt;/tt&gt; or, better, always log to stdout.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
